        -:    5:/*
        -:    6: * detect.c — independence detection for batch operations.
        -:    7: *
        -:    8: * Two operations are considered NOT independent if:
        -:    9: *   - Any two paths share a prefix where one path is a strict prefix of
        -:   10: *     another (i.e. one path is an ancestor directory of the other).
        -:   11: *   - Any two operations touch the same path.
        -:   12: *
        -:   13: * We are conservative: if there is any doubt, we return 0 (sequential).
        -:   14: *
        -:   15: * Algorithm:
        -:   16: *   For each ordered pair (A, B) of operations, check:
        -:   17: *     1. path_A == path_B  (same path -> not independent)
        -:   18: *     2. path_A is a proper prefix of path_B followed by '/'
        -:   19: *        (A is an ancestor of B -> not independent)
        -:   20: *     3. path_B is a proper prefix of path_A followed by '/'
        -:   21: *        (B is an ancestor of A -> not independent)
        -:   22: *
        -:   23: * O(n^2) in the number of operations; acceptable for the small batches
        -:   24: * expected in a container build runtime.
        -:   25: */
